# Structural Selectors ðŸ—ï¸

Target elements based on their position.

```css
li:first-child { font-weight: bold; }
li:last-child { border: none; }

/* Examples: Zebras striping */
tr:nth-child(even) { background: #f2f2f2; }
tr:nth-child(odd)  { background: #ffffff; }
```

# Pseudo-elements ðŸŽ­

Style specified **parts** of an element. Uses double colon `::`.

```css
::before { ... } /* Inserts content BEFORE element */
::after  { ... } /* Inserts content AFTER element */
```

## Example
```css
h1::before {
  content: "âœ¨ ";
}

p::first-line {
  font-variant: small-caps;
}
```

> âš ï¸ **Note:** `::before` and `::after` MUST have a `content` property to work!
